            <td>
                <asp:Label ID="Label11" runat="server" 
                    Text="&lt;p&gt;For overhauling the look and ambiance of your home, one best way is to rearrange the décor of your living room. It will bring refreshing change without costing a penny.Just take an innovative standpoint and make creative yet functional changes to observe the rebirth of your living room.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Visualize and reflectSince you want a cheerful transformation for your living room, think and visualize the novelty you are seeking. Once you have clarity over what kind of new decor you want, you would be able to that execute your plan perfectly. Contemplate if you want spaciousness, compactness, or complete refurbish of ambiance and proceed accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Focal point Decide for a new spotlight in your living room to give it a new look. If your sofa has been the focal point so far, change it to a striking wall panel, a unique artifact, a mini artificial landscape or an imposing showcase. The idea is to shift the focal point so that rest of the furnishings can be revamped to get a refreshing ambiance.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Repositioning of furniture Repositioning of furniture can bring a whole deal of new look to your living room. Change the directions of side tables; alter the wall faced by sofas; replace chairs with couches or vice versa and get the desired decor. However, do not meddle with the practicality of the furniture positions else someone would keep on tripping every now and then.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mixing and matching Revamp your living room by mixing and matching various furnishings. For example,interlace your sofa set with matching settee; amalgamate some bamboo furniture as a complimentary décor; display an ethnic artifact alongside a swanky lampshade. Such innovative combination will infuse a sense of novelty and make for an interesting décor.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A Visual charisma Establish a visual charisma in your living room with some inherent aesthetic sense that would reflect you and your home’s character. Place and replace the furnishings in your living room until you get a sense of entirety in the ambiance with a perfect balance between formality and comfort.&lt;/p&gt;"></asp:Label>
            </td>
