        <tr class ="content">
            <td style="width: 203px">
                <asp:Image ID="Image3" runat="server" Height="300px" 
                    ImageUrl="~/Pictures/lightning.jpg" Width="300px" />
            </td>
            <td>
                <asp:Label ID="Label16" runat="server" 
                    Text="&lt;p&gt;Glass votives always add a soft and elegant atmosphere to any place they’re placed. Whether its Christmas, Diwali or any other occasion, glass votives are always on the top of the décor list.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Well, leave aside festivals, glass votives also form an essential part of our home décor.&lt;/p&gt;Well, when we talk about glass votives, it doesn’t have to be some extravagant or a at an exorbitant price. You can make your own by using your own by using the simple materials lying in your house.&lt;p&gt;There are a million ways to use old stuff, simple glasses into votives.Drinking Glasses These are votives created from simple drinking water glasses. You could get these from a nearby shop in a local market. Use glass paints with the choice of your color and decorate it with some fancy handmade netted paper. Use colored beads and stones to enhance the look.&lt;/p&gt;"></asp:Label>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="title">
            <td colspan="2">
                <asp:Label ID="Label13" runat="server" Text="Decorating a kids room"></asp:Label>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="content">
            <td style="width: 203px">
                <asp:Image ID="Image4" runat="server" Height="300px" 
                    ImageUrl="~/Pictures/kids.jpg" Width="300px" />
            </td>
            <td>
                <asp:Label ID="Label17" runat="server" 
                    Text="&lt;p&gt;To keep you with your kids’ shifting tastes can be a tiring and daunting task, not to mention expensive. Right from your baby’s first nursery to your teenager’s bedroom, decorating it is tricky to get that right look. Here is what our expert has to say:Which colours should I choose for my 5 year old son’s room?When it comes to painting a room, it is advisable to choose neutral colours. The reason for this is simple: you can add bright artwork against a subtle back ground.My kid wants her favourite cartoon painted on the wall. Please suggest what to do?A kid likes and dislikes change very often. My son was little when I did his room with is favourite Spiderman and not even a year has passed that he has started to ask for a change. Ben 10 has replaced Spiderman. So, now you get what I want to say.It is always better to have your kid’s favourite cartoon on easily changeable accents such as bedding or wall art. Also, you could go for removable wall papers.How do I keep my kids toys tidy and also ensure that they are within his reach?You may use go for stylish play bins with and without wheels, plastic crates or you could even use low shelves for keeping your kid’s toys.What kind of furniture should I go for my 4 year daughter’s room?You may go for furniture that doubles up as storage space. This would help you keep your kid’s room uncluttered and at the same time would help you store his/her goodies properly. You may buy a bed that has drawers on the base or benches that have storage space. However, you need to make sure that all the storage places are at a height that your child can reach&lt;/p&gt;"></asp:Label>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="title">
            <td colspan="2">
                <asp:Label ID="Label14" runat="server" Text="Give an old couch a new look"></asp:Label>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="content">
            <td style="width: 203px">
                <asp:Image ID="Image5" runat="server" Height="300px" 
                    ImageUrl="~/Pictures/Couch.jpg" Width="300px" />
            </td>
            <td>
                <asp:Label ID="Label18" runat="server" 
                    Text="&lt;p&gt;Is your living room screaming for a new sofa? Is your old couch not so old to be dumped in the store room? Isn’t it worth even to reupholster the sofa? Then consider a makeover of your sofa- give your old couch a new look! Are you asking how?Here are some ways to make your old sofa look new.Use a slipcover over sofaIf your sofa looks beaten up or if the print doesn’t match with your décor, you can place a slip cover over your sofa. This is the easiest way to freshen up your old couch. If possible, go for a custom made slipcover that fits tight.If not, you’ll get slipcovers in many sizes and styles and it will not be a problem to find one that fits seamlessly to your sofa.If you don’t find one that tightly fits your sofa, take a wooden spatula and push the fabric deep into sofa’s crevices. If yours is a leather couch, and the slipcover slides over, use nonslip carpet padding on the seat cushion to give a tout look to the sofa.Make your couch colourfully textured.If your sofa isn’t all worn out but has become boring, you can bring back the interest element rather quickly by adding pops of colours over it. Use new cushion covers of larger size or mixed sizes. New cushion covers are cheaper options. Use ruffled cushion covers to introduce texture. You may even use pillow shams to be different and make your sofa a little distinctive.Decorate sofa with beautiful sofa throws Placing a beautiful sofa throw on the back of a sofa will add a new dimension to your couch and give it an instant life! Crochet sofa throws are really nice. However, select the throws as per your décor style. You may select anything from among fur throws, satin throws, contemporary sofa throws with geometrical or abstract designs, anything that goes with your living room décor.Sometimes it only takes to plump up your cushions to bring back that crispy look to your old sofa. Some other times it needs to change the fabric that you may do with the help of throws and slipcovers. Little accessories can go a long way to make your old sofa look new.&lt;/p&gt;"></asp:Label>
            </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr class="title">
            <td colspan="2">
                <asp:Label ID="Label15" runat="server" 
                    Text="Purchasing furniture for a smaller bedroom"></asp:Label>
            </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr class="content">
            <td style="width: 203px">
                <asp:Image ID="Image6" runat="server" Height="300px" 
                    ImageUrl="~/Pictures/smallerbedroom.jpg" Width="300px" />
            </td>
            <td>
                <asp:Label ID="Label19" runat="server" 
                    Text="&lt;p&gt;Of all the rooms in your home, your bed room is obviously the most important one. It is more than a room where you sleep for eight hours a day. It is your personal space which you do not like to share with anyone else. Your bedroom perhaps reflects your personality most accurately. It should be a room where you would like to spend your time after a long day’s work. It should reflect your preference and not your designer’s.You should use the colors and furnishing wisely to make the room cheerful enough.  Choosing the right kind of fabrics is also very important. The room should be decorated in such a way that one would feel pleased at the idea of spending time there. The different components of the furnishing, the colors and the fabrics used should create a beautiful but much required harmony.The most important thing to consider while decorating your bedroom is choose the right kind of furniture. The right kind of furniture will make any bedroom look like your personal haven. The list of furniture will include the bed, wardrobes, the chest of drawers, the bedside tables, the tables and chairs, the dressing table etc.The type obviously depends on a number of things like your taste and preference, budget, requirements and usage, the theme of the room and most importantly the room itself.While buying furniture for your home you need to be practical. Buy furniture which suits your bed room and at the same time reflects your personality.If you have a small bed room you need not worry much about it. Today a wide range of furniture is available that will make your small bed room look bigger and better.You just need some time and patience to pick the right kind of furniture for your bed room. In a small bed room you need to ensure that the entire wall space is properly used. Wardrobes set in the wall or nightstands hung from the wall look great and save up a lot of space too.For small spaces, opt for rectilinear furniture and not curved ones. This is because the latter tend to take up much more space compared to rectilinear ones. The bed is definitely the center of attraction in a bed room. Choose a bed that suits your room and that does not make your room look cramped.If you require a television set in your room go for a flat screen one. It can be mounted up on the wall or placed on the dresser without any fuss. A skirted table beside the bed is the ideal way to store the magazines and books that you read.The bedside table can be kept free by hanging the reading lights on the wall. Mirrors can be used effectively to create the illusion of a much bigger bed room. Get a mirror and keep it somewhere where it reflects a window. Go for bed room units in pale wood or timbre.You should pick units which are tall and simple in design. Build shelves of varying patterns and colors on the walls to free up floor space. Lighting also plays an important role. Buy hanging lights and focus the maximum light on the bed itself.&lt;/p&gt;"></asp:Label>
            </td>
        </tr>
        
